section.section:
A person may possess:
A dead game bird or dead game mammal legally acquired for use as food;
A mounted specimen of a game bird or game mammal legally acquired for personal use;
Hair, antlers, feathers, feet, or skin of game birds or game mammals legally acquired for personal use; or
Deer antlers that have been manufactured into an article of commerce.

The prohibitions of paragraph (1) of this subsection do not apply to the:
Meat, pelt, carcass, or mounted specimen of any beaver, coyote, fisher, fox, mink, muskrat, nutria, opossum, otter, raccoon, skunk, or long-tailed weasel legally taken by the person;
Hide, hair, tail, or feet, excluding a mounted specimen of deer, squirrel, or rabbit legally acquired;
Feathers, skin, or feet, excluding a mounted specimen of upland and forest game birds legally acquired;
Except as prohibited by federal law, feathers of wetland game birds legally acquired; or
Antlers of deer legally acquired in another state and manufactured into an article of commerce in another state.
